Write a SystemVerilog task that:

Takes an integer dynamic array as input.

Calculates the sum of all elements.

Calculates the average value of all elements.

Displays both results using $display.

ðŸ§  Requirements:

Use a task, not a function.

Use a ref array parameter (so that large arrays donâ€™t get copied).

Use a for loop to calculate the sum.
..............................................................................................
module tb;
int arr[]='{10,20,30,40};
int sum,avg;
task sum_avg(ref int a[],output int s,av);
int temp_s;
for (int i=0;i<a.size();i++)
begin
temp_s+=a[i];
end
s=temp_s;
av=temp_s/a.size();
endtask
initial
begin
sum_avg(arr,sum,avg);
$display("sum:%d,avg:=%d",sum,avg);
end
endmodule
..................................................................................................
output:sum:        100,avg:=         25
